http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Calicut-varsity-former-professor-dead/article13987837.ece

M.P. Sreekumaran Nair, former Professor of History at the University of Calicut, died in Thiruvananthapuram on Thursday due to age-related illnesses. He was 85.Prof. Sreekumaran Nair, who secured a PhD from the University of Kerala, was in the U.S. from 1966, where he taught at the Brooklyn College, New York, and Lincoln University, Pennsylvania. On his return to India in 1969, he joined the Department of History at the University of Calicut.He was a visiting professor at various universities in Kerala and at the University of Indonesia, Jakarta, from 1985 to 1987.He has published four books and many research papers in leading research journals. He is survived by a son and three daughters. The cremation will take place at Santhikavadam, Thycaud, at 1 p.m. on Friday.